                <para>The fuel filter element sealing arrangement was revised to include a "beveled gasket" versus the
                    old square cut gasket. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9212163">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9212163" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9212163.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. New And Old Fuel Filter Element Gasket</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>When servicing the engine with a replacement fuel filter and gasket, position the new
                            gasket on the fuel filter with the beveled edge up so it contacts the fuel filter header.
                            Tighten filter 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 turns after gasket contacts filter header surface.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <para>The new fuel heater (Pkg.), P/N 1 816 602 C91, functions identically and is interchangeable with
                    the old fuel heater. Its appearance is different. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9212164">Figure 4.</hotlnk>
                </para>
